ndness could occur.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kibo>Kibo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(3/21/02 8:53:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1491.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Comics: Why I can't do them =P</span><hr size=1> Well, I share the same fate. What you should do first in order to get used to drawing people interacting is for one thing starting off with big squares because it's easier, and drawing little irrelevant things in each one using only stick figures. Once you've become comfortable with the stick figures at a little flesh to the structure. Try drawing blank bodies interacting. After you're comfortable with that then begin adding detail to your bodies. But start off with easy interactions and work your way up as you go. That's all I can help you with, but I know there's one thing for sure... PRACTICE PRACTICE PRACTICE!! We don't like practicing things that we can't do very well, but if we discipline ourselves to rise to the challenge then it's worth your while. It's all about Kung Fu. Kung Fu isn't the actual martial art. The martial art is Wu Su, Kung Fu is actually devoting time and effort into something. Kung = energy, fu = time. Use Kung Fu on your artwork.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uretrotorque.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RetroTorque</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(3/21/02 12:11:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1491.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Comics: Why I can't do them =P</span><hr size=1> You should learn when to stop. I like to draw god pictures but if a detail just isn't working right I let it go because it's not the little things that make a picture. It's the whole thing.<br><br>If something just isn't quite working just finish the picture. Don't worry about your art suffering. I've seen many a ruined picture because the artist didn't know when to stop. <p>Be well, do good work, and keep in touch. -Writer's Almanac NPR</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kibo>Kibo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(3/21/02 2:33:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1491.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Comics: Why I can't do them =P</span><hr size=1> RetroTorque is right. You've gotta think with the right side of your brain, not the left. The left side is the side that says &quot;this isn't right&quot; and all that self criticizem, and right side is the creativity side that says &quot;hey, it may not be the Mona Lisa but I'm not Leonardo da Vinci, so that works out&quot;. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uanimelibra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>animelibra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(3/25/02 5:12:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1491.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Comics: Why I can't do them =P</span><hr size=1> Well, I don't have to worry about not drawing on the right side of my brain because I'm left handed. But I still can't get this great storyline out of my head. I've started, but then I'll slightly change my style and It'll screw up the art. but I'll finish..............someday <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>just keep trying and see how it all works out.<br><br>maybe I should try that too..........hmmmmm....... <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showPrevMessage?topicID=1491.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showNextMessage?topicID=1491.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1491.topic&index=4><img src=http://www.polykarbon.com/bbsimage/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.emailToFriend?topicID=1491.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.threadControl?topicID=1491.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1491.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1491.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="ri